# Rust Code Standards

## Errors

```rust
// ❌ BAD
let user = repo.get(id).unwrap();
} catch {}

// ✅ GOOD
let user = repo.get(id).await?;
// Use thiserror + ApiError at handler boundary; log internal errors, return generic messages
```

- Use `thiserror` / `anyhow`; convert to `ApiError` at handler boundary
- Avoid `unwrap()` in production paths; use `?` and propagate
- Don't leak internal errors to clients

## Consistency

- Naming: snake_case, plural routes (`/users`, `/health`)
- Run `rustfmt` and `clippy`; address warnings
- Doc comments for public APIs and non-obvious logic

## Conventions

- Keep handlers thin; move logic to services
- Prefer explicit types over `impl Trait` for public APIs when clarity helps
